{"answer":"For variant OAM-V0320, the range impact comes from higher aerodynamic road load, not mass. Source row: variant_id=OAM-V0320 with curb_mass_kg unchanged, drag_coefficient and frontal_area_m2 defining aerodynamic drag area CdA = drag_coefficient × frontal_area_m2. A +0.020 increase in drag_coefficient raises CdA by 0.020 × frontal_area_m2, so aerodynamic drag force increases proportionally at speed under the dossier’s road-load basis. Because curb_mass_kg is unchanged, rolling/inertial mass terms do not change; only the aero term increases. Therefore the vehicle needs more power/energy to maintain the same speed, which reduces range, especially on higher-speed drive cycles where aero losses dominate. Please provide the tool-returned OAM-V0320 row values for drag_coefficient and frontal_area_m2 if you want the exact original CdA and increased CdA numerically stated."}

